[6.696803, "o", "\u001b[36magent:\u001b[0m Perfect! I've successfully built and tested the calculator module. Let me summarize what I've done:\r\n\r\n1. Created `calculator.py` with four functions:\r\n   - `add(a, b)` - adds two numbers\r\n   - `sub(a, b)` - subtracts b from a\r\n   - `mul(a, b)` - multiplies two numbers\r\n   - `div(a, b)` - divides a by b, raising ValueError when b is zero\r\n\r\n2. Created `test_calculator.py` that:\r\n   - Tests all four functions with various inputs\r\n   - Specifically tests the division by zero error handling\r\n   - Uses plain assert statements as requested\r\n   - Ends with \"ALL TESTS PASSED\" when all tests pass\r\n\r\n3. Verified the tests run successfully with python3, showing \"ALL TESTS PASSED\"\r\n\r\n4. Confirmed the module works correctly with direct testing including proper error handling for division by zero\r\n\r\nAll requirements have been met and the tests pass successfully.\r\n"]
