[6.549823, "o", "\u001b[36magent:\u001b[0m I've successfully built the calculator module as requested. Here's what I accomplished:\r\n\r\n1. **Created `calculator.py`** with four functions:\r\n   - `add(a, b)` - adds two numbers\r\n   - `sub(a, b)` - subtracts b from a  \r\n   - `mul(a, b)` - multiplies two numbers\r\n   - `div(a, b)` - divides a by b, raising ValueError when b is zero\r\n\r\n2. **Created `test_calculator.py`** that thoroughly tests:\r\n   - All four arithmetic operations with various inputs\r\n   - Proper error handling for division by zero using plain assert statements\r\n   - Ends with \"ALL TESTS PASSED\" when successful\r\n\r\n3. **Verified the implementation** by running the tests with python3, which confirmed:\r\n   - All tests pass successfully\r\n   - Functions work correctly for normal operations\r\n   - Division by zero properly raises ValueError with the expected message\r\n\r\nThe calculator module is complete and functioning as specified. All requirements have been met and the code is ready for use.\r\n"]
